title: "Testing Next.js Route Handlers with Vitest"
category: patterns
tags: [testing, nextjs, vitest, mocking, route-handlers]
date: 2026-03-11
severity: medium
applies_to: [apps/web]
---

# Testing Next.js Route Handlers with Vitest

## Problem

Next.js App Router route handlers (e.g., `app/api/process/route.ts`) import server-only modules like `@supabase/ssr`, `next/headers`, and Drizzle ORM. These can't run in a test environment without real server infrastructure. How do you unit/integration test route handlers without spinning up a Next.js server?

## Solution

Mock at the module boundary using `vi.mock()` before dynamically importing the route handler. Three key patterns:

### 1. Mock auth + DB before importing the route

```typescript
// Set up mocks BEFORE importing the handler
const mockClient = mockSupabaseClient();
vi.mock("@/lib/supabase/server", () => ({
  createClient: vi.fn().mockResolvedValue(mockClient),
}));

const mockDb = createMockDb();
vi.mock("@/db", () => ({ db: mockDb }));

