# D5a: Training-Row Schema with Provenance — Implementation Plan

> **For Claude:** REQUIRED SUB-SKILL: Use clavain:executing-plans to implement this plan task-by-task.

**Bead:** texturaize-bi6
**Goal:** Create a unified `training_rows` table that captures every user training signal (accept/reject/pick/free_text/withhold) with full provenance so that no field needs retrofit, and wire MCP + Scout emission paths to it from day one.

**Architecture:** A new append-only `training_rows` table (Postgres on Neon, Drizzle ORM) becomes the canonical training signal. Shared TypeScript types live in `packages/pipeline-worker/src/shared/` so both `apps/web` API routes and the pipeline worker agree on the row shape. Existing narrower tables (`elicitation_dpo_pairs`, `elicitation_rejections`, `elicitation_predictions`, `training_pair_feedback`) are kept untouched; we dual-write to `training_rows` from the same call sites. `internal_prediction` is captured at attempt-generation time (written into `elicitation_predictions` as a new column) and copied into the row at emission. Fatigue-accept detection runs as a pure function at emission time.

**Tech Stack:** TypeScript strict, Drizzle ORM, Neon Postgres, Clerk auth (publicMetadata for user_tier), Vitest, Hono (pipeline worker), Next.js App Router (apps/web).

**Prior Learnings:**
- `docs/research/q1-training-loop/q1-spec.md` — Per-channel objectives (BT re-ranker / DPO-Positive / SFT w/ rejection sampling). Training rows must carry `display_mode` ("first-reader" vs "second-reader") and `signal_type` ("agreement"/"correction"/"rejection") so the pipeline can slice by objective. Don't blend channels into one preference pool.
- `docs/solutions/logic-errors/insert-or-replace-destroys-verified-data-20260405.md` — Use append-only inserts for training rows. Never `INSERT OR REPLACE` on unique keys; lose human-verified overrides. Our schema has no uniqueness constraint — rows are immutable audit records.
- `docs/solutions/patterns/persisting-ephemeral-client-state.md` — Client-side dwell timers must be forwarded on emit. Use stable content-hash hunk IDs (`h-xxxxxxx`), not positional indices, so IDs survive reprocessing.
- `docs/solutions/patterns/nextjs-route-handler-testing.md` — Mock `@clerk/nextjs/server` auth + `@/db` before importing route handlers in vitest.

---

## Must-Haves

**Truths** (observable behaviors):
- Every MCP elicitation accept/reject/pick writes a row to `training_rows` with all 16 fields populated.
- Every Scout web surface accept/reject writes a row to `training_rows` with `surface_origin = "scout-web"`.
- `internal_prediction` field contains the model's predicted-preferred text, captured at the time the attempt was generated (never after the user sees alternatives).
- Fatigue-accept demotion fires when `dwell_ms < 2000 AND failure_mode_severity > 0.3 AND surface_origin = "scout-web" AND queue_position > 7`, writing `engagement_type = "fatigue_accept"` and `training_weight = 0`.
- `user_tier` is sourced from Clerk `publicMetadata.tier`, falling back to `"unknown"` if unset.
- Existing narrower tables (`elicitation_dpo_pairs`, `elicitation_rejections`) continue to be written alongside — nothing in the old pipeline breaks.

**Artifacts** (files with specific exports):
- `packages/pipeline-worker/src/shared/training-row-types.ts` exports `TrainingRow`, `TrainingAction`, `UserTier`, `SurfaceOrigin`, `SignalType`, `EngagementType`, `DisplayMode`.
- `apps/web/src/db/schema.ts` exports `trainingRows`, `trainingActionEnum`, `userTierEnum`, `surfaceOriginEnum`, `signalTypeEnum`, `engagementTypeEnum`, `displayModeEnum`.
- `apps/web/src/db/migrations/0024_*.sql` adds the `training_rows` table and the `internal_prediction_text` column on `elicitation_predictions`.
- `apps/web/src/lib/training-rows/fatigue.ts` exports `detectFatigueAccept(input) -> boolean`.
- `apps/web/src/lib/training-rows/user-tier.ts` exports `resolveUserTier(userId) -> Promise<UserTier>`.
- `apps/web/src/lib/training-rows/emit.ts` exports `emitTrainingRow(params)`.

**Key Links** (where breakage cascades):
- Attempt-generation code path (elicitation-rewrite → `elicitation_predictions` insert) must persist `internal_prediction_text` BEFORE any user-facing action endpoint can read it. If generation skips the write, the action endpoint will see NULL and we lose the day-zero invariant.
- `resolveUserTier()` must be called at emit time (not at attempt time) so tier changes during a session are captured on the action row.
- Fatigue detection runs AFTER `failure_mode_severity` is known — severity comes from the attempt's model output. Attempt-generation must thread severity into the predictions row.

---

